objectives.name: Primary Safety Objective (All Cohorts)
objectives.text: To describe the safety profile of 20vPnC in adults 18 years of age and older.

objectives.name: Primary Immunogenicity Objective 1 - Cohort 1
objectives.text: To demonstrate that the immune responses to the 13 serotypes in 13vPnC (1, 3, 4, 5, 6A, 6B, 7F, 9V, 14, 18C, 19A, 19F, and 23F) induced by 20vPnC in adults 60 years of age and older are noninferior to the immune response induced by 13vPnC.

objectives.name: Primary Immunogenicity Objective 2 - Cohort 1
objectives.text: To demonstrate that the immune responses to the 7 additional serotypes (8, 10A, 11A, 12F, 15B, 22F, and 33F) induced by 20vPnC in adults 60 years of age and older are noninferior to the immune response induced by PPSV23.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Cohort 2
objectives.text: To demonstrate that the immune responses to the 20 serotypes in 20vPnC induced in adults 50 through 59 years of age are noninferior to the immune responses induced by 20vPnC in adults 60 through 64 years of age.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Cohort 3
objectives.text: To demonstrate that the immune responses to the 20 serotypes in 20vPnC induced in adults 18 through 49 years of age are noninferior to the immune responses induced by 20vPnC in adults 60 through 64 years of age.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - All Cohorts
objectives.text: To describe the immune responses to 20vPnC in adults 60 years of age and older, 50 through 59 years of age, and 18 through 49 years of age.

endpoints.name: Prompted Local Reactions
endpoints.text: Reported prompted local reactions (redness, swelling, and pain at the injection site) within 10 days after vaccination.

endpoints.name: Prompted Systemic Events
endpoints.text: Reported prompted systemic events (fever, headache, fatigue, muscle pain, and joint pain) within 7 days after vaccination.

endpoints.name: Adverse Events
endpoints.text: Reported adverse events (AEs) within 1 month after vaccination.

endpoints.name: SAEs and NDCMCs
endpoints.text: Reported serious adverse events (SAEs) and newly diagnosed chronic medical conditions (NDCMCs) within 6 months after vaccination.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Informed Consent
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Evidence of a personally signed and dated informed consent document (ICD) indicating that the subject has been informed of all pertinent aspects of the study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Compliance
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Willing and able to comply with scheduled visits, treatment plan, and other study procedures.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Availability
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Expected to be available for the duration of the study and can be contacted by telephone during study participation.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Age Cohorts
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Cohort 1: Male or female adults 60 years of age and older. Cohort 2: Male or female adults 50 through 59 years of age. Cohort 3: Male or female adults 18 through 49 years of age.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Stable Disease
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Adults determined by clinical assessment, including medical history and clinical judgment, to be eligible for the study, including adults with preexisting stable disease, defined as disease not requiring significant change in therapy in the previous 6 weeks or hospitalization for worsening disease within 12 weeks before receipt of investigational product.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Contraception
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Cohort 1 only: Female subject of nonchildbearing potential or male subject not able to father children; male subject who is able to father children and willing to use a highly effective method of contraception as outlined in this protocol until at least 28 days after the last dose of investigational product. Cohorts 2 and 3 only: Female subject of childbearing potential or male subject who is able to father children, and willing to use a highly effective method of contraception as outlined in this protocol for at least 28 days after the last dose of investigational product; or female subject not of childbearing potential or male subject not able to father children.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Site Staff Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Investigator site staff members directly involved in the conduct of the study and their family members, site staff members otherwise supervised by the investigator, or subjects who are Pfizer employees, including their family members, directly involved in the conduct of the study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Investigational Product Participation
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participation in other studies involving investigational drug(s), investigational vaccines, or investigational devices within 28 days prior to study entry and/or during study participation. Participation in purely observational studies is acceptable.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Prior Pneumococcal Vaccine
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Previous vaccination with any licensed or investigational pneumococcal vaccine, or planned receipt through study participation.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Severe Allergic Reaction
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of severe adverse reaction associated with a vaccine and/or severe allergic reaction (eg, anaphylaxis) to any component of 20vPnC, 13vPnC, or any other diphtheria toxoidcontaining vaccine or PPSV23.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Serious Chronic Disorder
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Serious chronic disorder including metastatic malignancy, severe chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) requiring supplemental oxygen, end-stage renal disease with or without dialysis, clinically unstable cardiac disease, or any other disorder that, in the investigators opinion, excludes the subject from participating in the study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Acute or Psychiatric Condition
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Other acute or chronic medical or psychiatric condition including recent (within the past year) or active suicidal ideation or behavior or laboratory abnormality that may increase the risk associated with study participation or investigational product administration or may interfere with the interpretation of study results and, in the judgment of the investigator, would make the subject inappropriate for entry into this study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Invasive S. pneumoniae Disease
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of microbiologically proven invasive disease caused by S pneumoniae.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Immunosuppressive Therapy
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subjects who receive treatment with immunosuppressive therapy, including cytotoxic agents or systemic corticosteroids, or planned receipt through the last blood draw. If systemic corticosteroids have been administered short term (<14 days) for treatment of an acute illness, subjects should not be enrolled into the study until corticosteroid therapy has been discontinued for at least 28 days before investigational product administration. Inhaled/nebulized, intra-articular, intrabursal, or topical (skin or eyes) corticosteroids are permitted.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Immunodeficiency
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subjects with known or suspected immunodeficiency or other conditions associated with immunosuppression, including, but not limited to, immunoglobulin class/subclass deficiencies, generalized malignancy, human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) infection, leukemia, lymphoma, or organ or bone marrow transplant.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Bleeding Diathesis
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Bleeding diathesis or condition associated with prolonged bleeding that would, in the opinion of the investigator, contraindicate intramuscular injection.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Blood Products
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Receipt of blood/plasma products or immunoglobulin, from 60 days before investigational product administration, or planned receipt through study participation.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Pregnancy or Breastfeeding
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Pregnant female subjects or breastfeeding female subjects (known or suspected).

studyInterventions.name: 20vPnC (PF-06482077)
studyInterventions.description: 20-valent pneumococcal conjugate vaccine containing 20 S. pneumoniae serotypes conjugated to CRM197

studyInterventions.name: 13vPnC
studyInterventions.description: Licensed 13-valent pneumococcal conjugate vaccine used as active comparator in Cohort 1

studyInterventions.name: PPSV23
studyInterventions.description: Licensed 23-valent pneumococcal polysaccharide vaccine used as active comparator in Cohort 1

studyInterventions.name: Saline
studyInterventions.description: 0.9% sodium chloride injection used as placebo in Cohort 1

studyInterventions.name: Antipyretic/Pain medication
studyInterventions.description: Permitted for treatment of symptoms; prophylactic use not recommended on the day of vaccination

studyInterventions.name: Influenza vaccine
studyInterventions.description: Licensed inactivated influenza vaccine permitted if given >14 days from study vaccination

studyInterventions.name: Systemic corticosteroids
studyInterventions.description: Prohibited during study participation; requires 28-day washout if used short-term prior to enrollment

administrableProducts.name: PPSV23
administrableProducts.strength: 25 mcg of each of 23 polysaccharide serotypes per 0.5 mL

amendments.name: Amendment 1
amendments.summary: Added editorial changes throughout the document to improve clarity and to correct typographic errors. Revised Protocol Summary to reflect modifications. Expanded the age range for Cohort 1 to include subjects 65 years of age and older and added flexibility to clinical assessment wording. Updated study size and power information for Cohort 1 and clarified immunogenicity bridging analysis for Cohorts 2 and 3.

amendments.name: Amendment 2
amendments.summary: Section 1.3: Added benefit-risk assessment (country specific-amendment, required for Sweden by the Swedish Medical Products Agency [MPA]). European Clinical Trials Database (EudraCT) Number: Updated to 2018-004279-11.

conditions.name: Febrile Illness Delay
conditions.description: Criteria for delaying vaccination due to fever
conditions.text: Current febrile illness (body temperature >= 100.4F [38C]) or other acute illness within 48 hours before investigational product administration.

conditions.name: Corticosteroid Delay
conditions.description: Delay required after short-term systemic corticosteroid use
conditions.text: If systemic corticosteroids have been administered short term (<14 days), subjects should not be enrolled until therapy has been discontinued for at least 28 days.

conditions.name: Vaccine Interference Delay
conditions.text: Receipt of any inactivated vaccine within 14 days or any live vaccine within 28 days before investigational product administration.

conditions.name: Pregnancy Status
conditions.description: Requirement for female subjects of childbearing potential
conditions.text: A negative urine pregnancy test result is required immediately before administration of the investigational product.
